# HTML5 Development Rules

This rule applies to: *.html

## Overview
Guidelines for writing semantic, accessible HTML5 code.

## HTML Best Practices
- Use proper HTML5 semantic elements (header, nav, main, section, article, footer)
- Ensure proper document structure with correct heading hierarchy
- Include appropriate meta tags for SEO and viewport settings
- Implement accessibility features (ARIA attributes, alt text, keyboard navigation)
- Use descriptive class names that reflect component purpose
- Avoid excessive nesting of elements
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible

## Component Structure
- Cards should use the `.card` component class
- Section titles should use the `.section-title` component class
- Primary buttons should use the `.btn-primary` component class
- Implement responsive navigation with mobile menu toggle

## Accessibility Requirements
- All images must have appropriate alt text
- Interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use ARIA attributes when necessary
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Ensure sufficient color contrast for text readability